His wife, Nolwandle Mantashe, will continue to self-quarantine at home. The couple tested positive for Covid-19 on Tuesday last week. In a statement, the government said the Minister was "admitted to hospital on the advice of their family doctor for better medical attention and monitoring". South Africa has the highest number of confirmed Covid-19 cases on the continent and the fifth in the world, after the United States of America, Brazil, India and Russia. It has about 360 000 cases and just over 5 000 deaths. --BBC--